<dl id="n36062c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36062c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36062c"> 62(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> weepers</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[On mourning clothes:]</font> Men to wear black, without buttons on the sleeves or pockets, plain muslin or Irish cambrick cravats and <mark>weepers</mark>, shamoy shoes and gloves, crape hatbands, and black swords and buckles; undress&mdash;Dark grey frocks. <small> A. Peter, <a name="APDF2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#APDF2"><cite title="source">Dublin Fragments, social and historic</cite></a> (1925) 28</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
